The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | UBI maps tech route to growth
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      UBI maps tech route to growth
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	Calcutta, Sept. 30: City-based United Bank of India (UBI) will spend Rs 77 crore to expand its ATM network by 1,000 units, improve net-banking and launch phone-banking.         
	Within a month we shall provide online stock-trading facility to our customers, UBI chairman and managing director Bhaskar Sen said. The bank already provides demat account facility.         
	We have plans to launch mobile banking, utility payment services and online trading facility in a months time, he said.         
	The UBI will introduce core-banking in all the 1,044 branches of its four regional rural banks by September next year. It is planning to reach out to 4,341 unbanked villages in 11 states under its financial inclusion project.                                                                                                                                             
